                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 830.51/1266.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-15T22:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 14, 8 p.m. Minister of Finance, Saviñon, agrees to pledge alcohol and
                    tobacco taxes but believes collection of same should not be surrendered at this
                    time to the Receivership. He believes two radical governmental innovations
                    should not be looked for at one time and that the country should digest
                    financial expert proposition before Receivership assume control internal
                    reorganization. He gave me to understand that he believed in said control
                    ultimately but not now and urged that Department stand by original program for
                    control by Receivership on failure to make payments. The money is needed at
                    once. The news, carefully spread, that Washington would finance Provisional
                    Government has had most salutary effect. Tobacco tax is really a stamp tax which
                    includes tobacco.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
